        <item>
            <title>LOGman 3.0 Beta joins the party</title>
            <pubDate>Mon, 25 Jul 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
            <link>https://www.joomlatools.com/blog/2016/07/logman-beta-joins-the-party/</link>
            <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.joomlatools.com/blog/2016/07/logman-beta-joins-the-party/</guid>
            <description>
                <![CDATA[
                
                    <img width="800" src="https://www.joomlatools.com/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-cover.jpg" alt="" />
                
                <p>With <a href="https://www.joomlatools.com/blog/2016/06/docman-30-beta2-is-available/">DOCman</a> and <a href="https://www.joomlatools.com/blog/2016/06/fileman-30-beta2-is-available/">FILEman</a> beta packages already available, it’s time for LOGman to join the party. We are happy to announce the first beta for LOGman 3.0.</p>

<!--more-->

<p>This new major version includes:</p>

<ul id="markdown-toc">
  <li><a href="#redesigned-user-interface" id="markdown-toc-redesigned-user-interface">Redesigned User Interface</a></li>
  <li><a href="#additional-activity-filters" id="markdown-toc-additional-activity-filters">Additional activity filters</a></li>
  <li><a href="#routing-support-in-frontend" id="markdown-toc-routing-support-in-frontend">Routing support in frontend</a></li>
  <li><a href="#linker-new-editor-plugin" id="markdown-toc-linker-new-editor-plugin">Linker, new editor plugin</a></li>
  <li><a href="#other-minor-improvements" id="markdown-toc-other-minor-improvements">Other minor improvements</a></li>
  <li><a href="#what-is-next" id="markdown-toc-what-is-next">What is next?</a></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="redesigned-user-interface">Redesigned User Interface</h2>

<p>Just like DOCman and FILEman, LOGman also got a new look with a modern and responsive UI, completely redesigned and focussed on improving the user experience on mobile devices.</p>

<figure>
    <picture>
        
        <source media="(min-width: 400px)" srcset="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-all-components.jpg?w=590&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-all-components.jpg?w=885&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 1.5x,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-all-components.jpg?w=1180&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 2x" />
        
        <source media="(min-width: 0px)" srcset="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-all-components.jpg?w=400&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-all-components.jpg?w=600&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 1.5x,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-all-components.jpg?w=800&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 2x" />
        <img class="image-blog-styled" src="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-all-components.jpg?w=590&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90" alt="Overview all logged actions." />
    </picture>
    
    <figcaption><p>Overview all logged actions.</p>
</figcaption>
    
</figure>

<h2 id="additional-activity-filters">Additional activity filters</h2>

<p>LOGman now allows you to better control what is being logged and/or displayed. We added granular filtering control over the actions from resources of each component.</p>

<figure>
    <picture>
        
        <source media="(min-width: 400px)" srcset="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-filters.png?w=590&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-filters.png?w=885&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 1.5x,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-filters.png?w=1180&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 2x" />
        
        <source media="(min-width: 0px)" srcset="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-filters.png?w=400&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-filters.png?w=600&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 1.5x,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-filters.png?w=800&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 2x" />
        <img class="image-blog-styled" src="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-filters.png?w=590&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90" alt="Filter the LOGman logs when creating a Menu Item." />
    </picture>
    
    <figcaption><p>Filter the LOGman logs when creating a Menu Item.</p>
</figcaption>
    
</figure>

<p>The same filter is also made available for filtering notifications that get sent by the <a href="https://www.joomlatools.com/extensions/logman/documentation/plugins/activity-notifier/">LOGman - Activity Notifier plugin</a>.</p>

<h2 id="routing-support-in-frontend">Routing support in frontend</h2>

<p>Resource links in a frontend activity stream now link to frontend pages when possible:</p>

<ul>
  <li>The resource is exposed by at least one published menu item</li>
  <li>The menu item and the resource are accessible by the current logged user</li>
</ul>

<p>This has been a most requested but very challenging feature. Joomla does not make it easy to find URLs from resources that get exposed in the frontend. Luckily we don’t give up easily and got it working.</p>

<figure>
    <picture>
        
        <source media="(min-width: 400px)" srcset="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-frontend.png?w=590&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-frontend.png?w=885&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 1.5x,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-frontend.png?w=1180&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 2x" />
        
        <source media="(min-width: 0px)" srcset="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-frontend.png?w=400&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-frontend.png?w=600&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 1.5x,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-frontend.png?w=800&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 2x" />
        <img class="image-blog-styled" src="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-frontend.png?w=590&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90" alt="Resource links are now clickable in the frontend." />
    </picture>
    
    <figcaption><p>Resource links are now clickable in the frontend.</p>
</figcaption>
    
</figure>

<h2 id="linker-new-editor-plugin">Linker, new editor plugin</h2>

<p>Linker is a new editor plugin that takes advantage of the new frontend routing support. This plugin allows for easy linking of site resources while editing content.</p>

<p>By simply searching by title, you are prompted with a list of linkable site resources to insert into the content editor. These links will take your users to the resource page they are pointing to.</p>

<figure>
    <picture>
        
        <source media="(min-width: 400px)" srcset="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-linker.png?w=590&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-linker.png?w=885&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 1.5x,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-linker.png?w=1180&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 2x" />
        
        <source media="(min-width: 0px)" srcset="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-linker.png?w=400&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-linker.png?w=600&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 1.5x,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-linker.png?w=800&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 2x" />
        <img class="image-blog-styled" src="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/logman-beta/logman-linker.png?w=590&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90" alt="Modal with list of linkable site resources." />
    </picture>
    
    <figcaption><p>Modal with list of linkable site resources.</p>
</figcaption>
    
</figure>

<p>This makes for a nice little companion while drafting any kind of content and the only one of its kind!</p>

<h2 id="other-minor-improvements">Other minor improvements</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Added E-mail layout support to LOGman - Notifier plugin</li>
  <li>Added Romanian and Japanese languages</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="what-is-next">What is next?</h2>

<p>At this point we are aiming for a second beta release within a couple of months. The stable release will follow shortly after.</p>

<p>Most of the remaining development tickets are minor improvements compared to the new functionality added in this beta release.</p>

<p>The most important remaining features are:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Logging of request data for security applications and audits</li>
  <li>A plugin for logging page hits</li>
  <li>A simpler developer API for easier integration with LOGman</li>
</ul>

<p>We encourage you to <a href="https://support.joomlatools.com/downloads/extras/logman20/14-beta-versions">download</a> this beta release and give it a try. We are most interested in your feedback to get the stable version out as soon as possible.</p>

<p>Thank you for your support!</p>

