            <title>DOCman Notify 2.1 is out</title>
            <pubDate>Thu, 19 May 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
            <link>https://www.joomlatools.com/blog/2016/05/docman-notify-2-1-is-out/</link>
            <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.joomlatools.com/blog/2016/05/docman-notify-2-1-is-out/</guid>
            <description>
                <![CDATA[
                
                    <img width="800" src="https://www.joomlatools.com/images/blog/2016/mail-box.jpg" alt="" />
                
                <p>Good news! Over the past few weeks we have worked on improving our DOCman Notify plugin.</p>

<p>We’re excited to bring you some awesome new features:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Document groups notifications</li>
  <li>Control the actions that trigger notifications</li>
  <li>Debug notifications</li>
  <li>Customizable emails</li>
</ul>

<!--more-->

<h2 id="what-is-docman-notify">What is DOCman Notify?</h2>

<p>Whether you are running a Joomla powered intranet or website, you often want to keep a close eye on what your users are doing. Especially when they are allowed to edit documents or upload new files. With DOCman Notify it’s super easy to set up email notifications.</p>

<h2 id="whats-new">What’s new?</h2>

<h3 id="notify-document-groups">Notify document groups</h3>

<p>When enabled, the plugin will notify users of user groups with access to the document. The maximum amount of users to be notified this way is 25. If  this number is exceeded these notifications will not get sent and a warning message will get displayed when debug mode is enabled.</p>

<figure>
    <picture>
        
        <source media="(min-width: 400px)" srcset="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/docman-notify-21/notify-plugin-settings.png?w=590&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/docman-notify-21/notify-plugin-settings.png?w=885&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 1.5x,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/docman-notify-21/notify-plugin-settings.png?w=1180&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 2x" />
        
        <source media="(min-width: 0px)" srcset="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/docman-notify-21/notify-plugin-settings.png?w=400&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/docman-notify-21/notify-plugin-settings.png?w=600&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 1.5x,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/docman-notify-21/notify-plugin-settings.png?w=800&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 2x" />
        <img class="image-blog-styled" src="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/docman-notify-21/notify-plugin-settings.png?w=590&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90" alt="Configure who receives notifications" />
    </picture>
    
    <figcaption><p>Configure who receives notifications</p>
</figcaption>
    
</figure>

<h3 id="control-the-events-that-trigger-notifications">Control the events that trigger notifications</h3>

<p>You may now decide which events trigger notifications in the plugin settings.</p>

<p>Additionally to <strong>add</strong>, <strong>edit</strong> and <strong>delete</strong> events, we added support for:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Submit</strong>: when a document is submitted from the front-end</li>
  <li><strong>Publish</strong>: when a document is published</li>
  <li><strong>Assign</strong>: when a document is assigned (owner change)</li>
  <li><strong>Download</strong>: when a document is downloaded</li>
</ul>

<figure>
    <picture>
        
        <source media="(min-width: 400px)" srcset="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/docman-notify-21/notify-plugin-events.png?w=590&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90,
