<h2 id="configuration">Configuration</h2>

<p>FILEman now ships with its own configuration manager and no longer makes use of the Joomla com_media configuration settings. Configuring the component is now <strong>easy and straightforward</strong>.</p>

<figure>
    <picture>
        
        <source media="(min-width: 400px)" srcset="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/fileman_30_configuration.png?w=590&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/fileman_30_configuration.png?w=885&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 1.5x,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/fileman_30_configuration.png?w=1180&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 2x" />
        
        <source media="(min-width: 0px)" srcset="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/fileman_30_configuration.png?w=400&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/fileman_30_configuration.png?w=600&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 1.5x,
                https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/fileman_30_configuration.png?w=800&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90 2x" />
        <img class="image-blog-styled" src="https://joomlatools.imgix.net/images/blog/2016/fileman_30_configuration.png?w=590&amp;auto=format&amp;q=90" alt="Screenshot of the new FILEman configuration UI" />
    </picture>
    
    <figcaption><p>Screenshot of the new FILEman configuration UI</p>
</figcaption>
    
</figure>

<p>The new configuration manager provides full control over the location to store files, file size limitations, thumbnails support and allowed file types. It also features a new <strong>email notification list</strong> so that users get notified when a file is uploaded.</p>

<p>We hope that you are as excited as we are with this new major release of the component. We have put a lot of <strong>love and effort</strong> to make this happen! Some more features are still being worked on for the stable release.</p>

<p>We encourage you to <a href="https://support.joomlatools.com/downloads/extras/fileman20/13-beta-versions">download</a> this beta release and <strong>give it a try</strong>. We are most interested on your feedback to get the stable version out as soon as possible.</p>

<p>Enjoy!</p>

